By ensuring that the code follows a coding standard, it is easier
to read the code and also spot errors.

Lets use the checkstyle command in gradle to find coding standard
violations and rectify them.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use Assertions in TaskList and MainWindow As TaskList methods are used in some commands, there is a need to ensure that what it returns is correct. Since the parameters passed affects what is returned, checking the parameters are important too. For MainWindow, assertion is will be used to ensure that for every command, an output is given.
commitResults.messageBody:
Using Java Assertions allows us to check for runtime errors created
by the programmer. We will then be able to find any error in the code
or future errors that may be caused due to future changes.

Lets add assertion in different methods that are commonly called.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve code quality There are some unnecessary code and complicated expressions used.
commitResults.messageBody:
To improve readability it is important to improve the code
quality. Also complicated expressions are broken down into
different variables so that errors can be spotted easily.

Lets remove unused code and also identify complicated
expression that uses a mix of function calls and hardcoded values.
The complicated expression will be broken into different variables.
